                <note rend="inline" type="source">323.2322/4: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Chargé in Peru</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Mayer</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-08-30T15:00:00-04:00"
                            >August 30, 1930—3 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>93 [<hi rend="italic">99?</hi>]. You are authorized to proceed as outlined in
                    your No. 167, August 29, 5 p.m., with respect to Mr. and Mrs. Larranaga and baby
                    and Mrs. Martinez and two small children. It is desired, however, that the
                    permission which you may request for their embarkation shall be entirely
                    informal and that no effort shall be made to justify your action under any
                    formal treaty or convention.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Castle</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
